<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--RunwayMishap     11-12 0165</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Runway Mishap,0169</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pilot `Prop Starts' Plane, Watches it Leave Without Her</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OCEAN CITY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pilot who had trouble starting her
plane Saturday got out, cranked the propeller by hand and watched
helplessly as the plane and its lone passenger taxied out of
control and ran into a wall.
   ``I guess it wasn't starting and she was trying to prop start
it,'' Ocean City patrolman T. Neiman said. ``I guess that worked.''
   The passenger was taken to Shore Memorial Hospital in nearby
Somers Point and treated for a minor ankle injury, Neiman said. No
one else was injured, he said. He would not release the women's
names.
   The aircraft, a single-engine Cessna 15-M, taxied across the
tarmac at Ocean City Municipal Airport and hit the wall of an
adjacent condominium complex before coming to a stop, he said.
   Neiman said the Federal Aviation Administration and police in
the seaside town 60 miles south of New York City were investigating
the mishap.
</TEXT>
