<FIRST>u i AM-Malaysia-Helicopter     11-12 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Malaysia-Helicopter,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report Says All 21 Aboard Crashed Helicopter Were Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pilot has spotted the wreckage
of an air force helicopter that crashed in northern jungle late
last week, and all 21 people aboard were believed dead, the
national news agency said Sunday.
   The helicopter and its three-member crew were ferrying 15 police
officers, one of their wives and two children when the craft was
reported missing Thursday.
   It was flying about 140 miles north of Kuala Lumpur at the time.
   An air force pilot in another helicopter located the wreckage in
jungle Sunday morning and reported no sign of survivors, the
Bernama news agency said, quoting air force Brig. Gen. Huang Chew
Siong.
   More rescue teams have left for the crash site to recover the
bodies, he was quoted as saying. All aboard the missing helicopter
were Malaysians.
   No cause of the crash was given.
</TEXT>
