<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--TrainFatals 1stLd-Writethru a0635 11-12 0194</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Train Fatals, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0635,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Dead, Two Hurt as Amtrak Train Strikes Van</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with names of injured, other details; CORRECTS
spelling in 4th graf to Tellefsen, sted Tollefson. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COON RAPIDS, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Amtrak passenger train rammed a van
at a crossing Saturday, killing three men and injuring two,
authorities said.
   Nobody aboard the train was injured and the engine wasn't
damaged in the crash in this suburb north of Minneapolis, said
Bruce Heard, an Amtrak spokesman in Washington, D.C.
   The railroad crossing arms were down and warning lights were
flashing when the crash occurred at 1:30 a.m. Saturday, said a
dispatcher at the Anoka County Sheriff's Department.
   The department identified the victims as Kenneth John Hansen,
24, of Minneapolis; Paul Kenneth Mills, 24, of Coon Rapids; and
Scott Robert Tellefsen, 23, of Coon Rapids.
   The two injured men, Thomas Carl Ramberg, 22, and Patrick
Michael O'Donnell, 24, both of Coon Rapids, were listed in stable
condition at Mercy Medical Center, according to nursing supervisor
Teresa Daigle.
   The train, known as the Empire Builder, was delayed about 48
minutes before continuing to Seattle, Heard said.
</TEXT>
