<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Train Accident Kills at Least 50 People</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BAGHDAD, Iraq (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train derailed near a northern city,
government-run newspapers reported Sunday. Local residents said at
least 50 people were killed and many others injured.
   The newspapers said the train derailed Friday south of the city
of Mosul at Baiji, about 130 miles north of Baghdad.
   They gave no specific number of casualties, saying only that
there were many.
   However, Mosul residents contacted by telephone said at least 50
people were killed and many others hospitalized.
   The news reports said three wagons turned over when the train
went off the track. They gave no definite reason for the derailment
but said it occurred in a rain storm.
   No other details were immediately available.
</TEXT>
