<HEAD>Shakes Eastern Aegean Island of Chios</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake rolled through the
eastern Aegean islands early Sunday, but police said no injuries or
significant damage were reported.
   The tremor, measuring 4.6 on the Richter scale, was felt mostly
near Chios' northern coast, said police.
   The Athens Seismological Institute said the quake struck at 6:50
a.m. with its epicenter in the Aegean seabed 138 miles northeast of
the capital.
