<SECOND>AM-BRF--Dukakis' Mother,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dukakis' Mother Released from Hospital; Kitty Dukakis Stays</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Euterpe Dukakis, mother of Gov. Michael S.
Dukakis, was released Sunday from Beth Israel Hospital where she
received a heart pacemaker, a spokesman for the hospital said.
   Mrs. Dukakis, 86, was admitted to the hospital last Monday after
suffering fainting spells. The pacemaker was implanted Friday.
   Hospital spokesman Antony Lloyd said Mrs. Dukakis was discharged
from the hospital shortly before noon Sunday.
   The governor's wife, Kitty Dukakis, remained hospitalized Sunday
at Brigham and Womens' Hospital. She was hospitalized after
experiencing a ``severe reaction'' to drinking rubbing alcohol last
Monday night while in a state of exhaustion with flu symptoms and
depression, her doctor said.
