teen-agers abducted Mrs. Tarr when she stopped at an automatic
teller machine Thursday night in Rochester Hills, then forced her
to return home.
   Guns, liquor, jewelry and part of a coin collection also were
taken from the home, police said.
   Tarr, a 25-year GM employee, was assistant manager of marketing
information and research for the Chevrolet Division headquarters in
Warren, said GM spokesman Jim Crellin. Mrs. Tarr was a life
insurance saleswoman.
